{
  "stem": "1721.3",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 314.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Although some of their friends or people that they knew who were in the camps talked more about it, they never would.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And, so, I grew up always with this idea that you just don't talk about it.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "But they held a lot in, too, and it just made life very, very bad for us all around.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And then, actually, I left home.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "I mean, I just left home when I was about 14.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not really.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not really, because both being German, it was pretty well-known the attitude that the German Jews had.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I think there was a lot of-- and I don't want to psychoanalyze German Jews, but I think there was a lot of ambiguity going on between German Jews.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "On the one hand, they always felt that they were sort of a little bit better and classier than the rest of the European Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But at other hand, they realized that didn't help them any.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "They had to go through the same horrors that everybody else went through, and I think it just never reconciled in their own lives.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And the other thing that bothered me.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It bothered me more in later life than it did at that time, but it bothers me more now as I look back is that they kept identifying with Germany all this time.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I know that we have met a lot of other Jews, Polish Jews, Russian Jews, Czechoslovakian, Dutch, all that.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "They recognize that they were not wanted by their country.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Their country turned their backs on them.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And they were very happy to be in America.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "With the German Jews, or at least the friends that we had, they only associated with German Jews, other German Jews who were in the camps.",
      "word_count": 26
    }
  ],
